LOCUS       HRV3C_site                 8 aa            linear   UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  HRV3C_site — LEVLFQGP, the 8-residue recognition/cleavage site for
            Human Rhinovirus 3C protease (EC 3.4.22.28); the protease cleaves
            between Q and G (LEVLFQ|GP), and is widely used to remove affinity
            or solubility tags from recombinant fusion proteins at 4 °C with
            high specificity and efficiency..
