     protein_domain  1..8
                     /label="HRV3C_site"
                     /synonym="PreScission protease site"
                     /synonym="3C protease cleavage site"
                     /synonym="HRV 3C site"
                     /synonym="LEVLFQGP"
                     /note="Human rhinovirus 3C protease recognition and
                     cleavage site (LEVLFQGP; Leu-Glu-Val-Leu-Phe-Gln-Gly-Pro).
                     The 3C cysteine protease cleaves the peptide bond between Q
                     (P1) and G (P1'), i.e. LEVLFQ|GP, leaving a Gly-Pro
                     N-terminal scar on the downstream protein. The site derives
                     from the natural HRV polyprotein processing sequence at
                     residues 1423-1430 of HRV3 (UniProt Q82081). It is the
                     recognition sequence used in the PreScission protease
                     reagent (a GST-HRV3C fusion). Source-verified to UniProt
                     Q82081 (POLG_HRV3) at 100% identity over all 8 aa. No
                     functional sub-features are present: this is a single
                     atomic cleavage-site element."
